# Li World Studio & Li Engine

**Canonical:** `docs/game-dev/world-studio-vision.md`  
**Tracker:** `docs/game-dev/PH-world-studio-program.md`  
**RFCs:** `docs/game-dev/specs/`

## Syntax

- Use Python-style **`def`** for functions in new code and docs (not `proc`).
- Keep `requires` / `ensures` / `decreases` on exported APIs.

## API ergonomics (authors + agents)

- Prefer **verb phrases** and **short aliases** in `lib.li`: `new_game_world`, `spawn_entity`, `new_field`, `step_field` — see [world-api-quickstart.md](../docs/game-dev/world-api-quickstart.md).
- Avoid cryptic suffixes in **public** APIs (`_stub` only for internal gates; expose a clear name beside it).
- One concept → one obvious name; document aliases in the quickstart, not only in RFCs.

## Product

- **One engine** for game + sim profiles — no CARLA/GROMACS/slicer forks.
- **Arbitrary physics:** `physics.custom` + `sim` law_mode — unphysical laws are first-class (games + research); see `arbitrary-physics-laws-rfc.md`.
- **Killer UX** (PH-UX): 60 fps, adaptive layouts, export wizards.
- **Agents:** MCP `li-engine` + `@cursor/sdk`; every path → `lic build`.
- **GPU:** CUDA + **ROCm/HIP** (no CUDA-only user kernels).
- **AM:** simulate + **export STL/3MF/G-code** to printers.
- **Drug design:** Lab-in-the-Loop + `studio.adaptive` + `li-chem` QM.
- **Publish:** `studio.publish` for paper-ready figures + repro bundles.
- **Compliance:** CRITICAL tier on `li-chem`, drug, AM export, `lic`.

## Do not

- Dump studio into `lic` compiler.
- Use `li-demo` for studio features by default.
- Add second physics engine for RL/sim.
- Add **external product stacks** (Python services, Redis/DB clients, etc.) — **port or redesign in Li** (`li-native-first.mdc`).
- Treat **`WorldSnapshot` as RealmHead only** — game state is **`GameWorld` ECS**; HPC state is **`SimField`** ([world-architecture-competitive-rfc.md](../docs/game-dev/specs/world-architecture-competitive-rfc.md)).

## Phases

PH-GD (editor) → PH-SIM (profiles) → domain packs (ROBO, AM, SCI, DRUG) → PH-QM / PH-VOXEL / PH-PUB in parallel where deps allow.
